title: COPY of Delaware Employment Equity Project: Community Workforce Campaign Survey

pages.title: Introduction
pages.description: Thank you for taking the time to complete this survey! The Delaware Workforce Development Board, through Project Work4Success, is collecting information from community members about their employment history, job skills, interests, and dreams, in order to better understand communities, in order to increase equity and opportunities for employment across the state. By elevating the experiences, capacities, and interests of people across your community, we are able to have more evidence to inform decisions that will positively impact our state. All of your responses will remain confidential and we are not going to register your name; if you would like to receive feedback on your responses, please provide your email address. Thank you!

pages.title: SKILLS MATCHER TOOL QUESTIONS
pages.description: The following questions are to help us, and you, understand more about your job skills! Shortly after you take this survey you will receive an email with more information about your responses, including some ideas of industries and jobs that might be a good fit for you. If your response to a question is "None", please select Beginner.

pages.title: Thank you!
pages.description: Thank you so much for participating in our survey. Your responses are extremely valuable to our work to close the employment and training gaps across the state. If you are interested in receiving feedback on your skills assessment as well as your $10 Visa gift card, please leave your email below. We will not contact you for anything other than these items.
